WEBVTT

00:06.382 --> 00:07.591
[Troy]
Previously on Shelter...

00:07.591 --> 00:09.468
[Ema] Holy shit,
that's Mrs. Friedman.

00:09.468 --> 00:11.345
So Dylan went missing after
one of his Little League games.

00:11.345 --> 00:12.346
So she must know something,
right?

00:12.346 --> 00:13.556
[Ema] Yeah.

00:13.556 --> 00:14.473
[Mickey]
Hey, maybe she was the one

00:14.473 --> 00:15.641
who took him to Dr. Kent.

00:15.641 --> 00:17.309
This is my new restaurant.

00:17.309 --> 00:18.561
How does Ken feel about it?

00:18.561 --> 00:20.229
I signed a two-year lease
today.

00:20.229 --> 00:21.147
You did what?

00:21.147 --> 00:22.732
Go fuck yourself.

00:22.732 --> 00:23.941
What the...

00:23.941 --> 00:25.192
[Angelica] Ema?

00:25.192 --> 00:26.610
What's Angelica Wyatt doing
in your house?

00:26.610 --> 00:28.279
[Whitney]
So Angelica Wyatt's your mom?

00:28.279 --> 00:29.697
[Ema] Yeah.

00:29.697 --> 00:31.323
I liked you before I knew
who your mom was,

00:31.323 --> 00:33.451
and I like you
just as much now.

00:34.368 --> 00:35.745
[Buck] Holy shit.

00:35.745 --> 00:41.333
Angelica Wyatt is Ema's mom.
[laughs]

00:41.333 --> 00:42.626
[Mickey]
I saw the butterfly tattoo.

00:42.626 --> 00:43.627
Agent gave it to me.

00:43.627 --> 00:44.545
They said the butterfly's

00:44.545 --> 00:46.922
an abeona tisi-something.

00:46.922 --> 00:48.841
That's the name of the charity
my parents worked for.

00:48.841 --> 00:51.343
This is my father's
final resting place.

00:51.343 --> 00:53.429
I feel like he's not even here.

00:53.429 --> 00:55.264
[Spoon]
So your dad knew Octoface.

00:55.264 --> 00:57.183
We need to run
that license plate number,

00:57.183 --> 00:59.226
find Octoface,
and get some fucking answers.

00:59.226 --> 01:02.062
Do you think that you could run
this license plate for me?

01:02.062 --> 01:03.773
It says that
the car is registered here

01:03.773 --> 01:05.191
to Antoine LeMaire,

01:05.191 --> 01:06.817
which I'm guessing
is Octoface's name.

01:06.817 --> 01:08.277
[Mickey]
We have to find a way inside.

01:08.277 --> 01:10.613
There's no way we're going
inside without a plan.

01:10.613 --> 01:11.989
[Mickey] Then we wait
for him to come back out.

01:13.532 --> 01:16.535
[dramatic music]

01:16.535 --> 01:22.082
♪ ♪

01:23.292 --> 01:27.087
[Rachel] Mickey, we should go
back to Kasselton now.

01:27.087 --> 01:28.255
It's like an hour drive,

01:28.255 --> 01:29.757
and your aunt is not
gonna be happy

01:29.757 --> 01:31.425
if you're not in your bed
when she wakes up.

01:31.425 --> 01:32.468
Uh, come on.

01:32.468 --> 01:34.637
Just a...a few more minutes.

01:34.637 --> 01:36.388
He'll be out any second.

01:36.388 --> 01:38.723
Yeah, but he could...

01:38.723 --> 01:39.934
I don't know.

01:39.934 --> 01:41.268
Maybe he could have
snuck out the back,

01:41.268 --> 01:43.604
or maybe
he's passed out inside.

01:43.604 --> 01:44.939
But he knows where Ashley is.

01:44.939 --> 01:47.483
Yeah.
But we don't know that, though.

01:47.483 --> 01:48.692
She could be fine.

01:48.692 --> 01:51.445
She could have run away,
for all we know.

01:51.445 --> 01:54.448
[muffled dance music playing]

01:54.448 --> 01:57.368
♪ ♪

01:57.368 --> 01:59.370
[door bangs]

02:00.287 --> 02:02.039
What the fuck?

02:02.039 --> 02:03.249
I'm spending a ton
of fucking money here

02:03.249 --> 02:04.792
to go to the fucking club!

02:04.792 --> 02:06.877
[person] Fuck off.

02:06.877 --> 02:08.795
[grunting]

02:08.795 --> 02:10.005
Mickey.

02:10.005 --> 02:12.675
[grunting]

02:12.675 --> 02:14.218
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

02:14.218 --> 02:15.469
Get the fuck out of here!

02:15.469 --> 02:16.637
Fuck. Fine.
Then let's go.

02:16.637 --> 02:18.347
[engine starts]

02:20.140 --> 02:23.352
[birds chirping]

02:23.352 --> 02:25.020
[soft music]

02:25.020 --> 02:26.480
[door clicks, creaks]

02:28.440 --> 02:31.026
[door closes]

02:31.026 --> 02:33.153
Oh, shit.
Shit. Shit.

02:33.153 --> 02:34.321
- Shit.
- What?

02:34.321 --> 02:35.406
Mickey's here.
You gotta go.

02:35.406 --> 02:37.116
Oh. Okay.

02:37.116 --> 02:38.033
I know the drill.

02:39.410 --> 02:40.661
Just like old times.

02:40.661 --> 02:41.787
Oh, yeah.

02:41.787 --> 02:42.829
Fun stuff.

02:42.829 --> 02:43.706
[chuckles]

02:50.462 --> 02:52.423
[gasps]

02:52.423 --> 02:53.841
[Mickey]
Uh, Rachel and I were busy

02:53.841 --> 02:55.509
doing a history school project,

02:55.509 --> 02:57.177
and I fell asleep.

02:57.177 --> 02:58.345
Yeah. That's cool.

02:58.345 --> 03:00.222
Oh. Okay.

03:00.222 --> 03:01.473
Yeah. No, you know what?
I'm sorry.

03:01.473 --> 03:03.434
That's not cool.

03:03.434 --> 03:05.144
- You should have called.
- Right.

03:05.144 --> 03:08.397
And no sleepovers
with your girlfriend.

03:08.397 --> 03:09.565
Still not my girlfriend.

03:09.565 --> 03:10.608
And uh, yeah.

03:10.608 --> 03:12.401
I said I would call next time.

03:12.401 --> 03:13.402
Okay.

03:14.069 --> 03:16.113
You're acting a little weird.

03:17.448 --> 03:18.699
No, I'm not.

03:18.699 --> 03:20.576
You definitely are.

03:20.576 --> 03:23.287
Well, uh,
sleep deprivation is real.

03:24.622 --> 03:25.915
Do you want some breakfast?

03:25.915 --> 03:27.291
Yeah, I'm starving.

03:28.334 --> 03:29.710
[Shira] Oh.

03:29.710 --> 03:33.297
I'm going to Dylan Shakes'
memorial today.

03:33.964 --> 03:36.884
Is there, uh, any chance
of you joining me?

03:38.177 --> 03:39.178
Uh, yeah.

03:39.178 --> 03:40.512
Great.

03:40.512 --> 03:42.765
I'll, um, pick you up
after school?

03:42.765 --> 03:43.766
Yeah.

03:45.017 --> 03:46.101
Okay.

03:47.436 --> 03:50.314
I, uh...

03:50.314 --> 03:51.774
I have to ask a favor.

03:53.233 --> 03:54.276
I'm listening.

03:54.276 --> 03:56.362
I, uh...

03:56.362 --> 03:58.280
I want to exhume my dad's body.

03:59.823 --> 04:01.158
What?

04:01.158 --> 04:03.869
[scoffs]
Why would you want to do that?

04:05.079 --> 04:06.497
For closure.

04:06.497 --> 04:07.790
Closure?

04:09.458 --> 04:11.085
Yeah.

04:11.085 --> 04:13.170
Digging up a grave

04:13.170 --> 04:16.966
is a pretty extreme way
to find closure, Mickey.

04:18.509 --> 04:21.595
What aren't you telling me?

04:22.846 --> 04:24.306
This is gonna sound crazy...

04:24.306 --> 04:26.684
It already does, so go on.

04:26.684 --> 04:29.853
...but I need to know
that my dad is in that grave.

04:29.853 --> 04:32.147
What makes you think
that he's not?

04:32.147 --> 04:33.357
I don't know.

04:33.357 --> 04:35.526
Uh, a feeling.

04:35.526 --> 04:36.986
Like, I...
I stand at his grave,

04:36.986 --> 04:38.278
and I don't feel anything.

04:38.278 --> 04:40.739
I don't feel like he's there.

04:42.032 --> 04:45.494
And some other stuff
that just doesn't add up.

04:47.329 --> 04:48.622
What stuff?

04:50.499 --> 04:54.128
Can you, uh, just trust me
on this one, please?

04:54.128 --> 04:59.633
♪ ♪

05:19.862 --> 05:21.739
Good morning.

05:21.739 --> 05:23.490
I spent the night at Shira's.

05:24.992 --> 05:27.286
How do you think
that looks to our son?

05:27.286 --> 05:28.537
You think Troy can't sense

05:28.537 --> 05:30.205
that there's something wrong
with our marriage?

05:30.205 --> 05:31.582
No.

05:31.582 --> 05:33.292
Because until a week ago,
I didn't either.

05:33.292 --> 05:34.835
Well, then you haven't
been paying attention.

05:34.835 --> 05:36.336
I don't want to fight, Hannah.

05:37.796 --> 05:41.425
When you didn't come home
last night,

05:41.425 --> 05:46.722
all the anger...
ran right out of me.

05:47.890 --> 05:52.895
I just feel...sad, mostly.

05:53.854 --> 05:56.690
I should have backed
your restaurant idea.

06:00.861 --> 06:04.531
And I'm sorry for that.
I've been a shit husband.

06:07.701 --> 06:09.495
Tell me how to make it right.

06:09.495 --> 06:12.372
[somber music]

06:12.372 --> 06:16.919
♪ ♪

06:16.919 --> 06:19.171
So Octoface never came out
the front of the club.

06:19.171 --> 06:23.801
Maybe he went out the back,
or maybe he's still inside.

06:23.801 --> 06:26.595
So that's a dead end for now.

06:26.595 --> 06:29.139
That just leaves us
with the good doctor.

06:29.139 --> 06:32.726
So Dr. Kent was positioning
as Ashley's father.

06:32.726 --> 06:34.937
But also,
he was Dylan Shakes' doctor

06:34.937 --> 06:37.272
and saw him the night
that Dylan disappeared.

06:37.272 --> 06:39.233
All these missing kids
are connected to Dr. Kent.

06:39.233 --> 06:40.400
Yeah.

06:40.400 --> 06:41.401
Man, we really
need to talk to him.

06:41.401 --> 06:42.653
Yeah, we do.

06:42.653 --> 06:44.863
Except we have no idea
where Bat Lady's man in black

06:44.863 --> 06:47.241
took him,
so that's also a dead end.

06:47.241 --> 06:48.992
So are we still saying
the same person

06:48.992 --> 06:53.497
that took Dylan almost
27 years ago also took Ashley?

06:53.497 --> 06:55.415
The Dylan Shakes memorial.

07:00.754 --> 07:03.966
Maybe the kidnapper
will show up.

07:03.966 --> 07:05.926
- You think?
- It happens.

07:05.926 --> 07:08.470
Perps get a kick out of seeing
the pain that they've caused.

07:08.470 --> 07:10.389
[Ema] That's really messed up.

07:10.389 --> 07:12.933
I'm gonna go with Shira,
so we can all go together.

07:12.933 --> 07:14.893
- Yeah, I'm in.
- Me too.

07:14.893 --> 07:16.770
[bell rings]

07:19.189 --> 07:21.150
- Hey.
- Hey.

07:23.318 --> 07:24.820
[PA system beeps]

07:26.280 --> 07:27.906
[Buck over PA system]
What is up, my Camels?

07:27.906 --> 07:29.533
This is Buck Renna here

07:29.533 --> 07:31.243
with your morning
announcements.

07:31.243 --> 07:32.870
And before we get
into anything,

07:32.870 --> 07:38.125
I just wanted to say a major
congratulations to Ema Winslow

07:38.125 --> 07:41.587
for landing the leading role
in Kasselton's fall production

07:41.587 --> 07:43.797
of Phantom of the Opera.

07:43.797 --> 07:45.507
Congratulations, Ema.

07:45.507 --> 07:49.094
You know, I think it is so
great that we are obliterating

07:49.094 --> 07:52.431
gender barriers
for this fresh perspective

07:52.431 --> 07:54.892
on a classic
Phantom character.

07:54.892 --> 07:56.518
Go for the Tony, Ema.

07:56.518 --> 07:58.187
It's called natural talent.

07:58.187 --> 07:59.855
[Buck over PA system]
Seriously, congrats, Ema.

07:59.855 --> 08:02.941
So happy for you,
especially since

08:02.941 --> 08:06.236
you'll be able to work
with your mom.

08:06.236 --> 08:07.988
That is right, Camels.

08:07.988 --> 08:11.742
Ema Winslow's mom
is none other

08:11.742 --> 08:17.331
than superstar of stage
and screen, Angelica Wyatt!

08:17.331 --> 08:19.207
[students murmuring]

08:19.207 --> 08:20.500
Did you know that?

08:20.500 --> 08:22.294
'Cause I didn't.

08:22.294 --> 08:24.546
[Mrs. Friedman] Where are you
going, Mr. Bolitar?

08:24.546 --> 08:25.714
Break a leg.

08:25.714 --> 08:27.549
You're gonna knock it
out of the park.

08:27.549 --> 08:30.093
Also, in other news,
we are gonna be finding out

08:30.093 --> 08:34.139
who has made the men's
varsity basketball team today.

08:34.139 --> 08:36.600
And I gotta say,
my money's on Truck...

08:38.434 --> 08:40.562
[groans]

08:40.562 --> 08:43.440
Oh. What the fuck?

08:43.440 --> 08:45.192
[door creaks]

08:46.318 --> 08:47.361
Can I help you?

08:47.361 --> 08:50.447
[tense music]

08:50.447 --> 08:57.454
♪ ♪

08:57.454 --> 08:58.789
[door clicks]

09:02.751 --> 09:05.504
Does your cousin Rob
still work at the Essex

09:05.504 --> 09:06.880
County Board of Health?

09:06.880 --> 09:07.714
He does.

09:07.714 --> 09:10.425
Um, are you interested?

09:10.425 --> 09:12.219
Because he's divorced.

09:12.219 --> 09:13.679
Mm. So tempting.

09:13.679 --> 09:15.472
- Mm.
- [laughs]

09:15.472 --> 09:17.599
Actually, I was...
[clears throat]

09:17.599 --> 09:22.688
...hoping that he could
help me exhume a body.

09:22.688 --> 09:24.731
Oh. Okay.

09:24.731 --> 09:25.816
Wow.

09:25.816 --> 09:28.902
Um, whose?

09:28.902 --> 09:30.654
My brother's.

09:30.654 --> 09:31.863
You want to dig up
your brother?

09:31.863 --> 09:35.367
Well, I don't actually want to.

09:35.367 --> 09:36.326
But...

09:38.120 --> 09:43.125
Mickey has doubts that Brad's
actually buried in the grave.

09:43.125 --> 09:44.543
Why does he have doubts?

09:44.543 --> 09:47.671
It's just a feeling.

09:47.671 --> 09:49.006
So you want to do all this

09:49.006 --> 09:51.925
based on the feeling
of a teenager?

09:51.925 --> 09:53.677
Yes.

09:53.677 --> 09:57.639
Because I have a similar...

09:57.639 --> 09:59.850
I don't know, feeling.

09:59.850 --> 10:01.852
Okay.
Based...based on what?

10:06.732 --> 10:08.525
[Brad on recording] Hi, Shira.

10:08.525 --> 10:09.818
It's Brad.

10:09.818 --> 10:11.278
Uh, I can't get into it,

10:11.278 --> 10:13.822
but we are back in the States.

10:13.822 --> 10:15.324
I can't really say much
right now,

10:15.324 --> 10:17.159
but you are the only one
that I trust.

10:18.327 --> 10:20.620
Please look out for Mickey,
okay?

10:20.620 --> 10:24.249
Just please call me back,
and, uh, I'm so sorry.

10:25.667 --> 10:29.212
And a few hours later,
he was dead.

10:29.212 --> 10:31.214
So wait, are you saying
that the car crash was...

10:31.214 --> 10:32.382
was not an accident?

10:32.382 --> 10:34.926
No.

10:34.926 --> 10:38.221
I mean, look,
Brad was given to paranoia.

10:38.221 --> 10:41.058
I think most likely
the crash was random,

10:41.058 --> 10:43.643
and this voicemail
was just shitty timing.

10:43.643 --> 10:49.191
But maybe exhuming Brad
will give us peace of mind.

10:49.191 --> 10:50.484
Yeah.

10:50.484 --> 10:51.860
[sighs]

10:51.860 --> 10:53.320
I'll call Rob.

10:53.320 --> 10:55.030
Thank you.

10:55.030 --> 10:57.199
[bell rings]

10:57.199 --> 10:58.492
Hey.

10:58.492 --> 11:01.411
[tense music]

11:01.411 --> 11:02.579
'Sup, Mayweather?

11:02.579 --> 11:04.414
- Oh, you heard about that?
- Yeah.

11:04.414 --> 11:07.542
Yeah, I guess you could say
I gave Buck a spoonful.

11:07.542 --> 11:08.877
[student 1]
Spoon, that was so awesome.

11:08.877 --> 11:10.796
- That's your worst one yet.
- Yeah.

11:10.796 --> 11:12.422
- [student 2] There he is.
- [student 3] There he is.

11:12.422 --> 11:13.673
Wow, word travels fast.

11:13.673 --> 11:14.883
Yeah.

11:14.883 --> 11:16.385
I didn't know
you had it in you.

11:16.385 --> 11:17.969
- I've got rage.
- [laughs]

11:17.969 --> 11:19.846
Did you get suspended?

11:19.846 --> 11:21.223
- Two days.
- Wow.

11:21.223 --> 11:22.599
I know. I asked for five.

11:22.599 --> 11:24.059
Why would you ask for more?

11:24.059 --> 11:27.312
I'm just really bad
at negotiating.

11:27.312 --> 11:29.815
Hey, have you, um...

11:29.815 --> 11:31.608
have you talked to Ema?

11:31.608 --> 11:32.943
No.

11:32.943 --> 11:34.361
All my calls
go straight to voicemail.

11:34.361 --> 11:35.362
Me too.

11:35.362 --> 11:36.822
I guess she just needs
some more time

11:36.822 --> 11:39.074
to, like, process it, you know?

11:39.074 --> 11:40.867
She's kept her mom a secret
her whole life.

11:40.867 --> 11:41.993
Yeah.

11:41.993 --> 11:43.829
Well, I guess
that just leaves us

11:43.829 --> 11:46.248
on our own for the memorial.

11:46.248 --> 11:47.749
I guess so.

11:49.709 --> 11:51.211
[door clicks]

11:51.211 --> 11:54.214
[indistinct chatter]

11:56.591 --> 11:57.801
[student 1] It's her!

11:57.801 --> 11:59.761
[student 2]
She looks nothing like her.

11:59.761 --> 12:02.681
[camera shutter clicking]

12:02.681 --> 12:05.350
Don't you even think about
posting that online.

12:05.350 --> 12:07.894
I will flush your phone down
the toilet, I swear to God.

12:07.894 --> 12:09.438
Okay. Bye.

12:09.438 --> 12:10.689
Whatever.

12:10.689 --> 12:11.857
[Whitney]
Forget about them, Ema.

12:11.857 --> 12:12.858
They're just a bunch
of fake bitches.

12:12.858 --> 12:14.651
You want to talk about
fake bitches?

12:14.651 --> 12:16.445
Ema, it's not like that.

12:16.445 --> 12:17.904
Why'd you tell him?

12:17.904 --> 12:19.322
Look, I know I fucked up, okay?

12:19.322 --> 12:21.616
- I feel terrible about it.
- Then why did you do it?

12:21.616 --> 12:23.869
I didn't think he would
tell everyone, okay?

12:23.869 --> 12:25.412
He promised.

12:25.412 --> 12:26.955
- He promised.
- Seriously, Ema, I...

12:31.877 --> 12:33.545
Buck blackmailed me.

12:33.545 --> 12:34.796
What are you talking about?

12:34.796 --> 12:36.339
[sighs]

12:43.013 --> 12:44.389
Buck found out
I bought my first

12:44.389 --> 12:47.809
500,000 followers on uDOu.

12:47.809 --> 12:50.812
He said he would expose me if
I didn't get some dirt on you.

12:50.812 --> 12:53.482
- Why would you buy followers?
- I don't know.

12:53.482 --> 12:55.650
I just did it, okay?

12:55.650 --> 12:57.444
I mean, who gives a shit
about a makeup artist

12:57.444 --> 12:59.488
with, like, two followers?

12:59.488 --> 13:03.241
That's...
that's fucking sad, Whitney.

13:03.241 --> 13:05.243
Okay, well, it happened, Ema.

13:05.243 --> 13:08.038
Look, if they find out,
I'll get kicked off the app.

13:08.038 --> 13:10.081
All my partnerships,
my sponsorships,

13:10.081 --> 13:11.708
everything will just be gone.

13:11.708 --> 13:13.960
I thought you didn't care
about any of that stuff.

13:13.960 --> 13:15.921
Of course I care, okay?

13:15.921 --> 13:19.257
It's my art, all right?
It's my reputation.

13:19.257 --> 13:20.634
And I'll be honest with you.

13:20.634 --> 13:22.969
It feels really nice
to have millions of people

13:22.969 --> 13:27.349
give a shit about you, okay?

13:27.349 --> 13:29.100
I never want
to talk to you again.

13:29.100 --> 13:30.477
Ema...

13:30.477 --> 13:32.145
I never want to see you again.

13:32.145 --> 13:36.066
- Ema, I'm sorry...
- Stay the fuck away from me!

13:36.066 --> 13:36.983
I'm sorry.

13:36.983 --> 13:40.695
Stay away.

13:40.695 --> 13:42.030
[♪ Porridge Radio:

13:42.030 --> 13:43.240
"Waterslide, Diving Board,
Ladder to the Sky"]

13:43.240 --> 13:50.247
♪ ♪

13:50.247 --> 13:54.000
♪ Waterslide... ♪

13:54.000 --> 13:55.919
[Shira] Mickey.

13:57.337 --> 14:00.674
Do you remember when I told you

14:00.674 --> 14:02.717
about the bullies
who dared your dad

14:02.717 --> 14:06.012
to go into Bat Lady's house?

14:06.012 --> 14:07.138
[Mickey] Of course.

14:07.138 --> 14:09.349
He got locked inside.

14:09.349 --> 14:10.642
Well...

14:14.104 --> 14:16.189
...I was the bully.

14:17.941 --> 14:20.068
Why would you do that to him?

14:22.070 --> 14:24.155
I don't know.

14:24.155 --> 14:27.325
It's...stupidity,

14:27.325 --> 14:30.954
peer pressure, sisterly hazing.

14:30.954 --> 14:33.957
I don't know.
I was a shit, okay?

14:33.957 --> 14:36.835
I just...I was going
through my own stuff,

14:36.835 --> 14:41.047
and I guess
I took it out on Brad.

14:41.047 --> 14:42.841
Oh.

14:42.841 --> 14:44.426
I've been wanting to tell you.

14:44.426 --> 14:48.346
And with the memorial today,
I...

14:48.346 --> 14:50.223
I felt I should.

14:52.934 --> 14:57.480
I mean, hating me again is...
totally reasonable.

14:57.480 --> 15:00.817
I don't hate you.

15:00.817 --> 15:02.027
Never have.

15:04.362 --> 15:09.242
You said that my dad was, uh,
never the same after that.

15:09.242 --> 15:10.243
Why?

15:10.243 --> 15:13.455
[tense music]

15:13.455 --> 15:16.541
[Shira]
He just sounded so terrified

15:16.541 --> 15:17.542
from inside the house.

15:17.542 --> 15:18.585
[knocking]

15:18.585 --> 15:20.170
And I couldn't go to him.

15:20.170 --> 15:21.254
Open up!

15:21.254 --> 15:25.508
So I ran to go get our parents.

15:25.508 --> 15:28.261
But by the time we got back,

15:28.261 --> 15:30.639
he was just sitting
on the front porch,

15:30.639 --> 15:32.641
as calm as can be.

15:32.641 --> 15:34.643
He was almost too calm.

15:36.519 --> 15:40.190
He never said
what happened inside.

15:40.190 --> 15:41.524
What do you think happened?

15:41.524 --> 15:43.818
[sighs]

15:43.818 --> 15:46.404
I don't know.

15:46.404 --> 15:51.117
I know that
it was something big.

15:51.117 --> 15:54.621
Something that changed
his whole life.

15:55.872 --> 15:58.583
And it was all my fault.

16:01.252 --> 16:03.713
So, um, we should get going.

16:03.713 --> 16:04.923
[clears throat]

16:07.801 --> 16:09.636
Yeah.

16:09.636 --> 16:12.639
[bells ringing]

16:16.726 --> 16:18.269
Oh, thank you.

16:18.269 --> 16:19.562
Yeah.

16:23.400 --> 16:25.568
Thank you so much.

16:27.445 --> 16:28.363
Oh, hi.

16:28.363 --> 16:29.906
Don't you look lovely?

16:29.906 --> 16:31.324
Never would have guessed

16:31.324 --> 16:32.826
that you were up all night
studying.

16:32.826 --> 16:33.827
Shira.

16:33.827 --> 16:34.869
What? I'm just saying.

16:34.869 --> 16:37.288
Thank you.
I hope we get an A.

16:37.288 --> 16:39.165
- You should.
- Hey.

16:39.165 --> 16:41.042
Do you have a second, Shira?

16:42.127 --> 16:43.253
Sure.

16:45.422 --> 16:47.173
- Studying.
- [Mickey] Yeah.

16:47.173 --> 16:49.634
- That's really original.
- She thinks we're in love now.

16:49.634 --> 16:51.094
Whatever works.

16:51.094 --> 16:53.096
- Hi.
- Hi, Arthur.

16:53.096 --> 16:55.682
- Oh, it's Spoon, actually.
- Oh. Why?

16:55.682 --> 16:57.517
- I don't know.
- I love it.

16:57.517 --> 16:59.144
- You guys want to sit down?
- Yeah.

16:59.144 --> 17:00.979
- Okay. Bye.
- See you.

17:04.648 --> 17:06.317
- Hey.
- Hey.

17:06.317 --> 17:07.694
You look gorgeous.

17:07.694 --> 17:10.320
And smart and funny
and empathetic,

17:10.320 --> 17:14.075
because your self-worth is not
bound to your physicality.

17:14.075 --> 17:15.743
[laughs] Wow.

17:15.743 --> 17:17.746
Someone's been doing
some introspection.

17:17.746 --> 17:19.414
Yeah.
It's ongoing work, actually.

17:19.414 --> 17:21.249
Mm.
It is for everyone, Troy.

17:24.210 --> 17:25.502
I really want
to thank you again

17:25.502 --> 17:27.714
for running that license plate.

17:27.714 --> 17:29.841
Yeah.
Hope you find Ashley.

17:29.841 --> 17:33.887
Yeah, um,
it definitely got us closer.

17:36.055 --> 17:38.099
You're in a cute mood today.

17:38.099 --> 17:39.893
I really want
to be worthy of you,

17:39.893 --> 17:41.269
so in 25 years,

17:41.269 --> 17:45.148
I'm not...creeping on you
on Facebook.

17:45.148 --> 17:46.441
I'm actually with you.

17:49.819 --> 17:51.821
Hey, a child's memorial service

17:51.821 --> 17:54.407
is probably not
the best place for PDA.

17:57.786 --> 18:01.372
So Hannah asked me
for a divorce this morning.

18:01.372 --> 18:03.166
Oh, my God.

18:03.166 --> 18:07.545
I'm...I'm so sorry, Ken.

18:07.545 --> 18:09.255
So you didn't know?

18:09.255 --> 18:11.591
I definitely didn't know.

18:14.052 --> 18:15.428
Look.

18:17.680 --> 18:20.058
I appreciate you being
a sympathetic ear

18:20.058 --> 18:21.851
to Hannah lately,

18:21.851 --> 18:24.395
which is why I was hoping
you would talk to her for me.

18:24.395 --> 18:26.523
She listens to you.

18:26.523 --> 18:29.234
Always has, since high school.

18:29.234 --> 18:30.944
I don't want to lose her.

18:34.697 --> 18:37.784
No, Ken.

18:37.784 --> 18:39.828
Why not?

18:39.828 --> 18:42.080
It's not my place.

18:42.080 --> 18:44.541
[Mrs. Friedman] Would you all
please take your seats?

18:44.541 --> 18:46.292
Excuse me.

18:46.292 --> 18:49.754
I want to thank you all
for coming here today

18:49.754 --> 18:51.881
to celebrate Dylan.

18:51.881 --> 18:54.259
It's beyond comprehension
that it's been

18:54.259 --> 18:59.055
27 years since he left us.

18:59.055 --> 19:01.975
I had the honor of being
his Little League coach,

19:01.975 --> 19:04.435
and I can tell you

19:04.435 --> 19:08.731
one of the most positive
influences

19:08.731 --> 19:10.108
in Dylan's life

19:10.108 --> 19:14.279
was his friendship
with Brad Bolitar.

19:18.032 --> 19:19.617
[person 1] Dylan!

19:19.617 --> 19:21.578
Focus!

19:21.578 --> 19:22.745
[person 2] Come on, Dylan!
You got this!

19:22.745 --> 19:23.746
Time out!

19:25.707 --> 19:27.208
Come on, Dylan.
You can do this.

19:27.208 --> 19:28.585
Say this to yourself.

19:28.585 --> 19:31.254
"You can't get a hit
if you don't swing the bat."

19:31.254 --> 19:33.548
Say that whenever
you doubt yourself, okay?

19:33.548 --> 19:36.050
You can't get a hit
if you don't swing the bat.

19:37.385 --> 19:40.221
Can't get a hit
if you don't swing the bat.

19:40.221 --> 19:43.808
Can't get a hit if
you don't swing the bat.

19:45.059 --> 19:46.686
Strike three!

19:47.979 --> 19:49.105
You're out!

19:51.566 --> 19:55.069
[Mrs. Friedman] It was
a very special relationship,

19:55.069 --> 20:00.199
and now they are both gone
too soon.

20:00.199 --> 20:03.202
Dylan had it rough,

20:03.202 --> 20:05.705
but he rose above it all

20:05.705 --> 20:09.000
to be gentle and kind
to everyone.

20:09.000 --> 20:10.793
[tense music]

20:10.793 --> 20:15.131
He brought out the best
in all of us.

20:15.131 --> 20:21.304
I'd like to believe that Dylan
is somehow here in this room.

20:23.806 --> 20:27.560
[ominous music]

20:27.560 --> 20:29.854
You think I don't know
what you've been doing

20:29.854 --> 20:31.648
to that poor boy?

20:31.648 --> 20:33.942
Do the right thing, Billy.

20:33.942 --> 20:38.947
And we gather here today
to remind ourselves

20:38.947 --> 20:41.866
that we will not rest

20:41.866 --> 20:46.663
until we find out for certain
what happened,

20:46.663 --> 20:50.917
and to make sure
the person who harmed our Dylan

20:50.917 --> 20:54.045
is brought to justice.

20:54.045 --> 20:58.341
♪ ♪

20:58.341 --> 21:00.259
Billy!

21:00.259 --> 21:03.513
You have a lot of nerve
showing up here today.

21:03.513 --> 21:05.139
I have a right to honor my son.

21:05.139 --> 21:07.475
You should be
ashamed of yourself.

21:07.475 --> 21:09.769
You put that poor boy
through hell.

21:11.437 --> 21:13.690
Do I got shame?

21:13.690 --> 21:15.525
Yeah, you bet I do.

21:16.818 --> 21:18.111
But I didn't kill him.

21:20.071 --> 21:21.614
Dr. Kent! Dr. Kent!

21:21.614 --> 21:22.615
Dr. Kent, wait.

21:22.615 --> 21:24.075
I'm sorry, I can't stay.

21:24.075 --> 21:25.785
Why'd you come
in the first place?

21:25.785 --> 21:27.120
I wanted to honor Dylan.

21:27.120 --> 21:28.496
Because he was your patient?

21:28.496 --> 21:30.289
Yes.

21:30.289 --> 21:31.666
Look, I have to go.

21:31.666 --> 21:34.627
You saw him the night
that he vanished.

21:34.627 --> 21:36.921
Did Dylan's father
take him to you?

21:38.548 --> 21:40.633
I didn't take him
to any doctor.

21:40.633 --> 21:44.012
But he was there that night
with an injury.

21:44.012 --> 21:47.015
What do you know about it?

21:47.015 --> 21:48.891
Billy?

21:48.891 --> 21:50.351
Billy, look at me.

21:51.436 --> 21:54.188
It's been 27 years.

21:55.231 --> 21:56.899
The time for secrets is over.

22:02.113 --> 22:03.489
He came home that night.

22:06.325 --> 22:08.661
Must have walked, I don't know.

22:08.661 --> 22:10.204
I was still angry.

22:10.204 --> 22:12.790
I can't even remember why.

22:13.958 --> 22:16.127
He struck out, you know?

22:17.170 --> 22:18.588
So what?

22:18.588 --> 22:23.301
Then he started talking
about how he lost the game.

22:25.178 --> 22:28.848
And he was so whiny and...

22:28.848 --> 22:30.850
and weak.

22:30.850 --> 22:32.435
[thunder booms]

22:34.854 --> 22:35.980
Oh, my God.

22:40.818 --> 22:43.321
What...what did you do, Billy?

22:44.989 --> 22:47.158
Something unforgivable.

22:49.118 --> 22:50.578
No! No!

22:50.578 --> 22:51.954
No!

22:53.331 --> 22:56.334
I don't know how anyone could
do that to their own child.

23:18.189 --> 23:21.651
[ominous music]

23:21.651 --> 23:24.695
♪ ♪

23:24.695 --> 23:26.697
Hey.

23:26.697 --> 23:28.074
Hey! Excuse me.

23:28.074 --> 23:31.077
[suspenseful music]

23:31.077 --> 23:38.084
♪ ♪

23:39.168 --> 23:40.753
[doorknob rattling]

23:57.145 --> 24:00.148
[eerie music]

24:00.148 --> 24:07.155
♪ ♪

24:37.852 --> 24:39.312
I know.

24:43.065 --> 24:45.443
You're Dylan Shakes.

24:51.616 --> 24:54.452
And what brought you
to that conclusion?

24:54.452 --> 24:56.787
A few things.

24:56.787 --> 24:59.290
But the sunglasses, mostly.

24:59.290 --> 25:01.000
I know what he did to your eye.

25:01.000 --> 25:02.752
No! No!

25:02.752 --> 25:04.921
- No!
- [sizzling]

25:04.921 --> 25:06.255
Please, you told me to come!

25:06.255 --> 25:07.757
Help! Help, please!

25:07.757 --> 25:10.218
Please! Please, help me!
You told me to come!

25:10.218 --> 25:12.178
- Please! Please!
- What?

25:15.139 --> 25:16.641
Oh, my God.

25:18.351 --> 25:20.519
It was Bat Lady.

25:22.188 --> 25:24.357
She rescued you.

25:24.357 --> 25:25.983
I guess you could say that.

25:27.735 --> 25:29.528
I'm sorry.

25:31.572 --> 25:32.782
Don't be.

25:35.034 --> 25:36.619
It gave me purpose.

25:36.619 --> 25:38.454
What?

25:38.454 --> 25:41.123
What purpose?

25:41.123 --> 25:44.418
The same one your father had.

25:44.418 --> 25:47.088
We rescue children.

25:49.674 --> 25:50.925
Abeona.

25:50.925 --> 25:52.593
Yes.

25:52.593 --> 25:57.848
All my life, my parents
have been working for Bat Lady

25:57.848 --> 25:59.934
to rescue children like you.

25:59.934 --> 26:03.896
Your father was
the bravest man I ever knew.

26:03.896 --> 26:05.773
He did what was necessary.

26:05.773 --> 26:08.067
She sees that same potential
in you.

26:08.067 --> 26:11.904
That picture she gave me
was photoshopped.

26:11.904 --> 26:13.239
That's not the Butcher.

26:13.239 --> 26:15.157
- [crashing]
- [glass shattering]

26:15.157 --> 26:18.452
[Dylan] The man in the picture
is the Butcher.

26:18.452 --> 26:20.162
He's your Butcher.

26:20.830 --> 26:22.873
That's what
she wants you to see.

26:24.709 --> 26:27.128
We all have our own Butcher.

26:30.673 --> 26:33.259
Why don't you tell anyone
you're still alive?

26:33.259 --> 26:35.845
Because it doesn't matter
anymore.

26:35.845 --> 26:38.306
It matters to Mrs. Friedman.

26:40.516 --> 26:41.976
You got work to do, kid.

26:45.604 --> 26:47.523
Saving Ashley.

26:47.523 --> 26:49.150
Yes.

26:54.155 --> 26:56.198
Dylan?

26:56.198 --> 26:57.491
Don't call me that.

26:58.868 --> 27:01.454
We're gonna dig up
my father's grave.

27:02.788 --> 27:04.123
What are we gonna find?

27:05.583 --> 27:07.418
The truth.

27:11.422 --> 27:14.425
[♪ Dehd: "Window"]

27:14.425 --> 27:21.432
♪ ♪

27:23.225 --> 27:26.520
♪ There's a hole
in my window ♪

27:26.520 --> 27:28.647
[phone buzzing]

27:28.647 --> 27:34.153
♪ I was wondering how
the rain was getting in ♪

27:34.153 --> 27:39.492
♪ Was it from
all this crying... ♪

27:39.492 --> 27:41.077
Hi.

27:41.077 --> 27:42.036
How are you?

27:44.872 --> 27:46.707
Bad.

27:47.333 --> 27:49.085
How was the memorial?

27:51.837 --> 27:54.131
Sad.

27:54.131 --> 27:56.008
Any word from Whitney?

27:56.008 --> 27:59.553
I told her to fuck off,
and I have six missed calls.

27:59.553 --> 28:01.263
Nice. As you should.

28:01.263 --> 28:02.723
[Ema] Spoon, I, uh...

28:05.476 --> 28:08.145
...I heard about what you did.

28:08.145 --> 28:09.146
With Buck.

28:09.146 --> 28:12.817
Oh, yeah. That.

28:12.817 --> 28:13.901
Well...

28:15.403 --> 28:18.155
[crying] I feel really stupid.

28:20.658 --> 28:23.244
I don't know why I trusted her.

28:24.412 --> 28:26.539
Ema, I'm actually
really proud of you.

28:27.706 --> 28:28.666
Why?

28:29.792 --> 28:35.089
Well, I didn't know you
too well before this, but...

28:35.089 --> 28:36.382
what happened
feels like something

28:36.382 --> 28:39.301
the old Ema wouldn't have done.

28:39.301 --> 28:42.888
Taking a risk
and putting yourself out there.

28:47.893 --> 28:49.937
Hey, Ema?

28:49.937 --> 28:51.564
What?

28:51.564 --> 28:54.233
Remember that time we kissed?

28:54.233 --> 28:56.569
You just ruined the moment.

28:58.070 --> 29:00.573
So I talked to Rob,

29:00.573 --> 29:04.660
and I set up a call
tomorrow for the exhumat...

29:04.660 --> 29:05.828
exhumation?

29:05.828 --> 29:07.163
I don't know.
Is that even a word?

29:07.163 --> 29:08.789
That's great. Thank you.

29:08.789 --> 29:10.291
[soft music playing]

29:10.291 --> 29:11.750
Hey, are you okay?

29:11.750 --> 29:13.752
You seem a little off.

29:13.752 --> 29:16.297
You asked Ken for a divorce?

29:16.297 --> 29:18.841
Ah.

29:18.841 --> 29:20.342
You talked to him
at the memorial.

29:20.342 --> 29:21.510
Yeah. Yeah.

29:21.510 --> 29:23.554
It was kind of a...a big shock.

29:25.598 --> 29:30.686
You know, I...I hope that you
didn't do this for me.

29:30.686 --> 29:31.854
What if I did?

29:31.854 --> 29:33.522
No, Hannah.

29:33.522 --> 29:36.942
Please don't blow up your life

29:36.942 --> 29:39.612
because you and I are
stuck in the past.

29:39.612 --> 29:42.323
Oh, is that...is that
all we're doing here?

29:42.323 --> 29:45.618
You know, when you left
that summer after high school,

29:45.618 --> 29:48.787
you just...you slammed the door
on any kind of a future.

29:48.787 --> 29:49.872
All right. Come on, Hannah.

29:49.872 --> 29:51.665
Just let me finish, okay?

29:51.665 --> 29:53.334
I never thought that
we would have another chance.

29:53.334 --> 29:55.836
And then boom,
you fucking showed up again!

29:55.836 --> 29:57.171
And...and now we do.

29:57.171 --> 29:58.255
This is insane.

29:58.255 --> 29:59.507
You know what I think?

29:59.507 --> 30:01.008
I think you're about
to run away again.

30:01.008 --> 30:02.343
So I'm gonna say now

30:02.343 --> 30:04.345
what I didn't get a chance
to say 25 years ago.

30:04.345 --> 30:05.846
I fucking love you.

30:05.846 --> 30:08.432
I love everything about you.

30:08.432 --> 30:09.892
I always have.

30:09.892 --> 30:14.522
And this is what I want
for the rest of my life.

30:14.522 --> 30:16.398
[sighs]

30:16.398 --> 30:18.108
Do you want the same?

30:21.654 --> 30:24.657
[muffled dance music playing]

30:24.657 --> 30:30.871
♪ ♪

30:34.166 --> 30:37.169
[indistinct chatter]

31:02.361 --> 31:03.195
Ashley.

31:03.195 --> 31:04.321
Huh?

31:09.451 --> 31:10.578
[bouncer] You let him in?

31:10.578 --> 31:12.746
- He had an ID.
- Yeah.

31:12.746 --> 31:14.832
[bouncer]
It's a fake, you moron.

31:14.832 --> 31:16.709
Hey, hey! There he is!
Get him!

31:16.709 --> 31:18.002
[manager]
If you don't fucking get him...

31:18.002 --> 31:19.962
- This way.
- [bouncer] Hey, you!

31:19.962 --> 31:21.797
[indistinct shouting]

31:21.797 --> 31:23.382
- Who are you?
- Candy.

31:27.928 --> 31:28.929
Shh.

31:29.972 --> 31:31.223
That him?

31:34.852 --> 31:36.312
We don't have much time.

31:40.941 --> 31:44.528
[♪ Puma Blue: "Hounds"]

31:44.528 --> 31:47.448
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

31:47.448 --> 31:48.365
What are you doing?

31:48.365 --> 31:50.075
Just play along, Mickey.

31:50.075 --> 31:51.368
Do I know you?

31:51.368 --> 31:53.370
No, but I know you.

31:53.370 --> 31:55.789
Ashley showed me your picture.

31:55.789 --> 31:57.041
She's my friend.

31:57.041 --> 31:59.627
We're like sisters.

31:59.627 --> 32:00.961
So she's here?

32:00.961 --> 32:01.879
- Yes.
- All right.

32:01.879 --> 32:03.005
Then take me to her.

32:03.005 --> 32:04.340
Mickey, listen to me.

32:04.340 --> 32:05.758
You can't help Ashley.

32:05.758 --> 32:07.092
It's too late.
She's in the dungeon.

32:07.092 --> 32:09.219
Dungeon?
What the fuck is that?

32:09.219 --> 32:11.263
It's where you go
when you've been sold.

32:11.263 --> 32:12.556
She's been sold?

32:12.556 --> 32:15.100
Yes, to a very wealthy man.

32:15.100 --> 32:16.977
For what?

32:16.977 --> 32:18.228
Whatever he wants.

32:18.228 --> 32:19.730
We gotta call the police.

32:19.730 --> 32:22.232
If you call the cops,
Buddy will kill her.

32:22.232 --> 32:24.610
But if you let
Ashley get sold...

32:24.610 --> 32:25.986
No. That's not an option.

32:25.986 --> 32:28.280
At least she'll stay alive.

32:28.280 --> 32:30.240
- Well, take me to her.
- It's a suicide mission.

32:30.240 --> 32:32.242
Let me get you out of here
while I still can.

32:32.242 --> 32:34.244
I don't think you understand.

32:34.244 --> 32:36.747
I'm not leaving here
without her.

32:44.213 --> 32:45.589
Make a right.

32:45.589 --> 32:48.467
The dungeon is
the last door on the left.

32:48.467 --> 32:50.886
- Thank you.
- But Mickey.

32:50.886 --> 32:52.262
Please think this over, okay?

32:52.262 --> 32:54.181
The door's locked.
Only Buddy has the key.

32:54.181 --> 32:55.683
He has some code on his phone

32:55.683 --> 32:57.309
that switches it
every few minutes.

32:57.309 --> 32:58.519
You won't get in.

32:58.519 --> 33:00.270
- And if he catches you...
- I'll be fine.

33:00.270 --> 33:02.064
Thank you for being such
a good friend to Ashley, okay?

33:02.064 --> 33:03.273
Mickey...

33:03.273 --> 33:05.943
I'm the reason why
Ashley's here again.

33:05.943 --> 33:07.319
What?

33:07.319 --> 33:08.529
It's true.

33:08.529 --> 33:10.280
After Abeona got her out
the first time,

33:10.280 --> 33:11.907
Buddy cloned my phone.

33:11.907 --> 33:13.951
He knew how close we were.

33:13.951 --> 33:15.744
When he saw Ashley
was still texting me,

33:15.744 --> 33:20.082
he ordered me to set up
a meeting with her, or...

33:20.082 --> 33:21.959
He'd kill you.

33:21.959 --> 33:25.170
So I betrayed my friend.

33:25.170 --> 33:26.797
This is all my fault, Mickey.

33:26.797 --> 33:28.173
Listen to me.

33:28.173 --> 33:30.259
You're making it up to her
right now by helping me.

33:30.259 --> 33:31.510
It's not enough.

33:31.510 --> 33:33.429
If I save her, it will be.

33:34.555 --> 33:35.514
Good luck.

33:35.514 --> 33:38.517
[tense music]

33:38.517 --> 33:45.524
♪ ♪

33:50.487 --> 33:51.822
Ashley?

33:54.283 --> 33:56.160
Ashley, is that you?

34:04.042 --> 34:05.377
[thud]

34:05.377 --> 34:06.670
[grunts]

34:11.675 --> 34:12.676
[indistinct shouting]

34:16.346 --> 34:19.349
[groaning]

34:27.357 --> 34:29.777
[Kylie]
What is this shit, Buddy?

34:29.777 --> 34:31.862
[Buddy] He's here to rescue
his girlfriend, Kylie.

34:33.614 --> 34:37.534
You do what you want with me,
but you let her go.

34:38.368 --> 34:41.330
Yeah, I'm afraid I can't, uh...

34:41.330 --> 34:43.956
I can't do that,
Mickey Bolitar.

34:43.956 --> 34:48.712
Ashley's new man is coming
to claim his prize tomorrow.

34:48.712 --> 34:50.505
And you...

34:50.505 --> 34:54.551
you already know way too much
to ever walk out of here alive.

34:57.179 --> 34:58.639
No. No.

35:02.810 --> 35:04.436
[zip ties zipping]

35:06.939 --> 35:08.190
Can I get started now?

35:08.190 --> 35:09.483
Oh, no.

35:09.483 --> 35:10.734
I'll handle this.

35:10.734 --> 35:12.903
You guys get back
to date night.

35:12.903 --> 35:14.404
You got it.

35:25.332 --> 35:27.417
[device beeps]

35:27.417 --> 35:29.169
I'm Abeona, Mickey.

35:29.169 --> 35:31.088
- Let's get you out of here.
- No. No, no.

35:31.088 --> 35:32.756
I'm not leaving here
without Ashley.

35:32.756 --> 35:33.841
No, you have to.

35:33.841 --> 35:35.342
It's too dangerous here,
Mickey.

35:35.342 --> 35:36.760
You just said you were Abeona.

35:36.760 --> 35:38.720
- So help me get her out.
- There's no time.

35:38.720 --> 35:39.763
What do you mean,
there's no time?

35:39.763 --> 35:40.806
Ashley has no time!

35:40.806 --> 35:41.807
Okay, Mickey.

35:41.807 --> 35:43.308
Mickey, look.

35:43.308 --> 35:46.812
This...this is so much more
complicated than you know,

35:46.812 --> 35:47.938
and I don't...

35:47.938 --> 35:49.815
I don't have time
to explain it.

35:49.815 --> 35:52.317
But your dad would
want me to protect you,

35:52.317 --> 35:53.944
so that's what I'm gonna do.

35:53.944 --> 35:55.237
You knew my dad?

35:55.237 --> 35:57.865
Yeah, Lizzy introduced us
when we were teens.

35:57.865 --> 36:01.451
Brad and I worked on
a lot of missions together.

36:01.451 --> 36:04.204
Our final one was last year,
in Europe.

36:09.126 --> 36:10.335
The camping trip.

36:11.628 --> 36:13.672
Dad? What happened?

36:13.672 --> 36:14.923
Nothing.

36:14.923 --> 36:16.884
[Mickey] He was washing
blood off his hands.

36:16.884 --> 36:18.969
We tried to save a dozen girls
from being trafficked,

36:18.969 --> 36:21.430
including Ashley.

36:21.430 --> 36:23.015
But the mission failed.

36:26.226 --> 36:29.730
Mickey, let me help you, okay?

36:37.821 --> 36:38.906
Yeah?

36:47.414 --> 36:49.082
Wait. Hold on. Hold on.

36:49.082 --> 36:50.292
Put your hands up.

36:52.878 --> 36:54.171
Come on. Let's go.

37:01.762 --> 37:04.765
[thrumming dance music playing]

37:04.765 --> 37:07.351
[indistinct chatter]

37:07.351 --> 37:13.106
♪ ♪

37:13.106 --> 37:14.691
You're gonna go out
the blue door

37:14.691 --> 37:16.485
at the top of the stairs, okay?

37:16.485 --> 37:18.236
Promise me
you'll get Ashley out.

37:18.236 --> 37:19.780
I swear it.

37:19.780 --> 37:22.491
Wait.

37:22.491 --> 37:25.243
There are rumors
that Brad's still alive.

37:25.243 --> 37:26.787
- Are they true?
- No.

37:26.787 --> 37:28.205
Because he was my friend.

37:28.205 --> 37:29.623
I...I just can't stand
the thought of him

37:29.623 --> 37:31.667
not in this world,
so if you know something,

37:31.667 --> 37:34.252
it would just put my mind
at ease.

37:34.252 --> 37:37.923
I wanted him to be alive
more than anything.

37:37.923 --> 37:38.882
But he's gone.

37:46.139 --> 37:49.142
[distant sirens wailing]

37:54.982 --> 37:55.816
Hello again.

37:58.735 --> 38:00.487
Hey. Hey.

38:00.487 --> 38:03.573
[grunting]

38:03.573 --> 38:06.326
[ominous music]

38:06.326 --> 38:08.203
♪ ♪

38:08.203 --> 38:09.705
I had to be sure Brad was dead.

38:09.705 --> 38:10.998
Buddy's in front.

38:10.998 --> 38:12.290
Tell him to wait for my text.

38:12.290 --> 38:15.293
- I want this problem gone.
- No.

38:15.293 --> 38:16.878
You lied to me!

38:16.878 --> 38:18.964
You fucking liar!

38:18.964 --> 38:20.507
Fuck!

38:20.507 --> 38:23.510
[dramatic music]

38:23.510 --> 38:29.016
♪ ♪

38:50.037 --> 38:51.913
[crickets chirping]

38:52.748 --> 38:55.333
Thank you for coming, Martha.

38:55.333 --> 38:58.503
I wasn't sure you would.

38:58.503 --> 39:02.632
I missed you at,
uh, Dylan's memorial.

39:02.632 --> 39:04.843
You know me.

39:04.843 --> 39:08.972
I have never been one
for sentimental reminiscing.

39:08.972 --> 39:11.266
His father showed up.

39:11.266 --> 39:12.559
What?

39:12.559 --> 39:15.020
He finally told me
the truth about what he did

39:15.020 --> 39:17.230
to poor Dylan
the night he disappeared.

39:17.230 --> 39:21.860
That bastard took
a cigarette to that boy's eye.

39:21.860 --> 39:23.403
You knew?

39:23.403 --> 39:26.656
I warned you, Martha, that he
was going to try to kill him.

39:26.656 --> 39:27.991
But you didn't listen.

39:27.991 --> 39:29.576
You told me to wait.

39:29.576 --> 39:33.663
I loved that little guy,
and I wanted to make him safe.

39:33.663 --> 39:35.832
Safe?
You wanted to adopt him.

39:35.832 --> 39:38.877
I thought I could
give him a better life.

39:38.877 --> 39:39.836
Better life?

39:39.836 --> 39:41.588
You lost all objectivity.

39:41.588 --> 39:43.423
Why are you bringing
this up again?

39:43.423 --> 39:45.967
His father would have never
allowed you to adopt him.

39:45.967 --> 39:47.677
How could you not see that?

39:47.677 --> 39:49.971
The only safe place
for Dylan Shakes

39:49.971 --> 39:52.182
was far away from that man.

39:54.059 --> 39:56.353
And that is where I sent him.

39:58.146 --> 40:00.232
You?

40:00.232 --> 40:02.984
I gave him shelter.

40:02.984 --> 40:04.778
I should have told you
long ago,

40:04.778 --> 40:06.822
but I could not trust
that you would not go

40:06.822 --> 40:08.240
to the authorities.

40:08.240 --> 40:11.076
So...oh, my God.

40:12.035 --> 40:15.080
Is...Dylan is still alive?

40:17.124 --> 40:18.542
Is he?

40:18.542 --> 40:20.544
Is he alive?

40:20.544 --> 40:23.088
Lizzy, is he okay?

40:23.088 --> 40:24.339
Where is he?

40:26.341 --> 40:29.302
Why am I here?

40:29.302 --> 40:32.222
[Sunglasses]
So I can thank you.

40:32.222 --> 40:35.225
[tender music]

40:35.225 --> 40:38.353
♪ ♪

40:38.353 --> 40:40.397
[exhales]

40:43.275 --> 40:44.109
Dylan?

40:44.109 --> 40:46.361
It's okay.

40:46.361 --> 40:48.113
I'm okay.

41:00.417 --> 41:03.253
Oh, there you are.

41:03.253 --> 41:05.380
[crying] Oh, God.

41:08.800 --> 41:11.803
[sobbing]

41:16.308 --> 41:19.311
[tense music]

41:19.311 --> 41:26.318
♪ ♪

41:29.863 --> 41:33.200
[grunting]

41:33.200 --> 41:34.868
[screams]

41:42.250 --> 41:44.628
Look, I know this sucks.

41:44.628 --> 41:48.048
If it comes to that,
I'll make it quick.

41:48.048 --> 41:50.050
[yelling]

41:51.343 --> 41:53.303
[gunshots]

41:55.847 --> 41:58.850
[♪ Lime Garden: "Clockwork"]

41:58.850 --> 42:00.143
♪ ♪

42:00.143 --> 42:01.895
♪ Wear my crown ♪

42:01.895 --> 42:03.897
♪ 'Round a desolate town ♪

42:03.897 --> 42:08.276
♪ Holding on to situations
that can't be seen or found ♪

42:08.276 --> 42:12.447
♪ It's like clockwork,
the way my head hurts ♪

42:12.447 --> 42:14.824
♪ Thinking back
on better days ♪

42:14.824 --> 42:16.910
♪ And maybe
changing up my ways ♪

42:16.910 --> 42:21.122
♪ It's like clockwork,
don't you think ♪

42:21.122 --> 42:22.749
♪ Circles 'round my head ♪

42:22.749 --> 42:25.627
♪ The ticking time bomb
keeps me out of bed ♪

42:25.627 --> 42:30.090
♪ It's like clockwork,
can't you see ♪

42:30.090 --> 42:32.968
♪ I guess I'm romanticizing
nothing yet again ♪

42:32.968 --> 42:35.553
♪ What fun we'll be ♪

42:35.553 --> 42:42.560
♪ ♪

42:43.561 --> 42:47.524
♪ Found out by now,
the trickling sound ♪

42:47.524 --> 42:51.945
♪ Is a visualized adjustment
of my inner few pounds ♪

42:51.945 --> 42:56.116
♪ It's like clockwork,
the way my head hurts ♪

42:56.116 --> 42:58.868
♪ Thinking back on
how we used to laugh ♪

42:58.868 --> 43:00.537
♪ And even sometimes play ♪

43:00.537 --> 43:04.833
♪ It's like clockwork,
don't you think ♪

43:04.833 --> 43:07.335
♪ Circles 'round my head ♪

43:07.335 --> 43:09.087
♪ The ticking time bomb
keeps me out of bed ♪

43:09.087 --> 43:13.508
♪ It's like clockwork,
can't you see ♪

43:13.508 --> 43:16.886
♪ It's like clockwork ♪

43:18.930 --> 43:21.683
[lion roars]
